Dear Ilya Grigorievich,

The editors are more than entranced with the material you sent us. Seldom have we had the occasion to peruse pages upon which a “human soul” has been so clearly imprinted. Your novel moves the reader with a face’s singular expression, to paraphrase Baratynski, the singer of the Finnish crags. It breathes “bitterness and tenderness.” Some of the descriptions, such as for example that of the theater,